-- max-finder-crystal.cell: find max, verify it's actually the max
-- Oracle: the result is in the list AND no element is greater

вҠў find-max
  given items вүЎ [42, 17, 93, 8, 65, 31]
  yield maximum

  вҲҙ Find the largest number in В«itemsВ».

вҠў verify-max
  given find-maxвҶ’maximum
  given items вүЎ [42, 17, 93, 8, 65, 31]
  yield none-greater

  вҲҙ Check: is there any element in В«itemsВ» that is strictly greater
    than В«find-maxвҶ’maximumВ»? Return false if none is greater (meaning
    the maximum is correct), true if something is greater.

  вҠЁ none-greater = false

вҠў crystallize
  given В§find-max
  given verify-maxвҶ’none-greater where none-greater = false
  yield В§find-max', is-faithful

  вҲҙ Read В«В§find-maxВ». It finds the maximum of a list.
    Write a вҠў= expression: max(items)

вҠў verify-crystal
  given В§find-max'
  given crystallizeвҶ’is-faithful
  yield approved

  вҲҙ Does В«В§find-max'В» use only вҠў= primitives?

  вҠЁ if approved and crystallizeвҶ’is-faithful then В§find-max' may replace В§find-max
